<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Anastasia on 10-25-99 01:57 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hi Lar,

thanx a lot for your preliminary report on Project C. Very much appreciated over here.
Also, I´m glad that we share the opinion of not wanting to start off some definition warfare over CRPG or whatever.

But then it´s very vague what you´re saying about Project C. Can´t blame you for that though. If I were creating the masterpiece of my life I´d also hate to share too much knowledge beforehand.
There is one thing I did not quite understand. 
You said that the player is controlling a heroin. I mean isn´t it much more so that heroin is controlling you and not the other way around. Well, looks like I gotta contact my drug counselor some time ;-)
Interaction with the game world and involvement in the story sounds OK though but didn´t surprise me too much (isn´t that what computer games are for ???).

1) No one did. Actually I`d love to see a game with no combat at all for a change but if there is even just a little itty-bitty of fighting in this game couldn´t you please make it round based. You know, I´m really slow on these mouse buttons. Or how about a slow motion switch for such lethargic players like me ?

2) Hey, that´s what I always wanted ever since. Control my schizophrenic alter ego.

3) Very good idea. Level systems really suck.

4) Guess it does. So, schizophreny as well, right ?!

5) I love inter-dependencies in questions.

6) Never-ending ? OK, no problem as long as I get to take my computer with me when they put me 6 feet under :-)

7) Thanx for giving no spoilers.

8) Release date is no more an issue since the game might be never-ending. Depends on No. 6 though.

9) Didn´t expect one ;-)

Well, I´m looking forward to finding out more about Project C. Good luck with your current build and do everybody a favor by renaming the game from Project C to something else (Project C sounds more like the Iraq chemical weapons program than a computer game).

Have at it,
Anastasia









</TEXTAREA>
